# --- Additions from AIMS Desktop heritage ----------------------------
# python3-mpi4py — MPI for Python, parallel computing. AIMS curriculum
#     uses MPI for the HPC modules (Cooperative Numerical Methods,
#     parallel linear algebra).
# python3-biopython — bioinformatics (sequence analysis, BLAST APIs);
#     used in AIMS Biological Modelling.
# python3-skimage — scikit-image, image processing and computer vision.
# python3-igraph — graph theory algorithms (different API from networkx,
#     faster for large graphs); shipped by AIMS Desktop 2020.
# python3-rpy2 — call R from Python (and vice-versa). Lets students
#     prototype models in Python and validate with R libraries.
# python3-tables — PyTables, HDF5 dataset wrapper with query syntax.
#     Alternative to plain h5py for tabular scientific data.
# python3-pygments — syntax highlighting library (used by Jupyter,
#     mkdocs, sphinx, …).
# python3-reportlab — programmatic PDF generation; common in statistics
#     reports and grading rubrics.
# NOTE: python3-pyfftw is intentionally NOT shipped — the Debian package
# was dropped from Trixie. Install on demand via `pip install pyfftw`
# (it picks up the libfftw3-dev headers we ship in aims-os-core).
 python3-mpi4py,
 python3-biopython,
 python3-skimage,
 python3-igraph,
 python3-rpy2,
 python3-tables,
 python3-pygments,
 python3-reportlab,
