Description: AIMS OS — scientific and mathematical software stack
 This metapackage installs the scientific computing layer that
 justifies AIMS OS's existence: the Python SciPy ecosystem (numpy,
 scipy, pandas, matplotlib, seaborn, sympy, scikit-learn, statsmodels,
 networkx) with the classic Jupyter Notebook + ipywidgets + the
 JupyterLab back-end libs (the JupyterLab UI itself is install-on-
 demand via `pipx install jupyterlab` since Debian does not yet
 package it; SageMath also install-on-demand on Trixie — see note below);
 Maxima and wxMaxima for symbolic computation;
 GNU Octave with the scientific add-on modules (symbolic, statistics,
 optim, control, signal); R with the tidyverse, ggplot2, knitr and
 rmarkdown packages; the full TeX Live distribution with French and
 English language packs, texlive-science, XeTeX and LuaTeX support,
 TeXstudio and biber for thesis writing; GeoGebra and gnuplot for
 geometry and plotting; gdb and valgrind for debugging C / C++ /
 Fortran code; and the OpenBLAS, LAPACK, FFTW, HDF5, GMP and MPFR
 development headers for compiling numerical software.
 .
 The 2025-2026 AIMS curriculum adds a Big Data / data engineering
 layer (Dask + distributed; PyArrow, Polars and DuckDB stay install-
 on-demand since Trixie does not yet package them), an NLP and
 Generative-AI layer (NLTK; spaCy, gensim and HuggingFace
 Transformers are install-on-demand for the same reason), Computer
 Vision (OpenCV alongside scikit-image), a climate-sciences layer
 (xarray, netCDF4, Cartopy), modern crypto primitives for the
 Post-Quantum Cryptography course, an Ethical Hacking / Network
 Security toolkit (nmap, Wireshark, tcpdump, John the Ripper,
 hashcat, aircrack-ng, scapy) plus Sleuth Kit, foremost and binwalk
 for the Auditing Computer Forensics course, and the PostgreSQL,
 MariaDB, Redis and MongoDB clients (plus psycopg2 and pymongo)
 for the Database course.
 .
 PyTorch, TensorFlow, JAX, Keras and other rapidly-evolving ML
 frameworks (and Qiskit for the Quantum Computing course, plus
 PyArrow, Polars, DuckDB, spaCy, gensim and HuggingFace Transformers
 since Trixie does not yet package them) are deliberately NOT
 included — installation via `mamba install`
 (Miniforge3 ships in aims-os-core's chroot) or `pipx install` is
 the recommended path so students get current versions.
